  "texts": [
    "While the Agent-as-Tool and cooperative tools provide a flexible perspective for multi-agent collaboration, achieving decentralized autonomous coordination remains challenging for current LLMs.",
    "Decentralized autonomous coordination represents each agent dynamically self-organizing the allies team and disconnecting redundant agents.",
    "Therefore, to gradually evaluate autonomy and cooperation capabilities of LLMs, Tool-RoCo defines four progressive cooperative paradigms that gradually increase in complexity: starting from centralized cooperation, through centralized self-organization and decentralized cooperation, and fi-nally arrive at whole self-organization.",
    "We explain these four paradigms in the next section.",
    "Based on the centralized LLM agent or decentralized multiple LLM agents, and whether other agents are treated as tools, Tool-RoCo defines four progressive paradigms corresponding to increasing levels of agent autonomy."
  ],
